austen_books()

Find the most common words in both Pride & Prejudice and Sense & Sensibility.

pride <- austen_books() %>%
  filter(book == "Pride & Prejudice")
Pride_words <- 
  pride %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, text)

Pride_words
pride_count %>%
  arrange(desc(count)) %>%
  slice(1:10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = word, y = count)) +
  geom_col() +
  ggsave("pride_with_stop.jpg")
Saving 7 x 7 in image

Pride_words %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word, sort = T) %>%
  slice(1:10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = word, y = n)) +
  geom_col() +
  ggsave("pride_most_common.jpg")
Joining, by = "word"
Saving 7 x 7 in image

sense <- austen_books() %>%
  filter(book == "Sense & Sensibility")
sense_words <- 
  sense %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, text)

sense_words
sense_count <- sense_words %>%
  group_by(word) %>%
  summarise(count = n()) 
`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
sense_count
sense_words %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  count(word, sort = T) %>%
  slice(1:10) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = word, y = n)) +
  geom_col() +
  ggsave("sense_most_common.jpg")
Joining, by = "word"

sense_words_sent <- sense_words %>%
  anti_join(stop_words) %>%
  left_join(get_sentiments("bing"))
Joining, by = "word"
Joining, by = "word"
